    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-applicable",
      "rationale": "The validation experiments for this CFD hemolysis assessment use a single FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry with a fixed, well-characterised design. ASME V&V 40 'Test samples' factor addresses variability across multiple physical specimens (e.g., manufacturing lot-to-lot variation). Because the COU is a computational sensitivity study on a single nominal geometry — not a population-level assessment requiring sample statistics — no multi-specimen sampling strategy is required or applicable at MRL 2. The factor is therefore not applicable to this assessment scope."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-applicable",
      "rationale": "The 'Equivalency of input parameters' factor applies when validation experiments are conducted on a surrogate or scaled model that differs from the COU device, requiring formal equivalency arguments to bridge the gap. In this assessment, the validation experiments are performed on the identical FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry and at the identical COU operating conditions. No surrogate geometry, scaled model, or analogue fluid is employed. Consequently, there is no equivalency gap to characterise, and this factor is not applicable to the present COU."
